<section id="faq">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
    <h2>Straight answers.</h2>
    <div style="margin-top:36px;max-width:820px">
      <details><summary>What does "zero upfront fees" mean?</summary><div class="a">If your civil rights case qualifies for our litigation referral network, we place it with an attorney who represents you on contingency — you pay nothing out of pocket, and the attorney's fee comes only from a recovery. If there's no recovery, you owe no attorney's fee.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Do you provide legal advice?</summary><div class="a">Legal advice is provided only by licensed attorneys — either our in-house counsel or the network attorney handling your referral. Our paralegal document-preparation service is not legal representation; for pro se clients, we prepare documents based on the information you provide and assist with procedural compliance and formatting.</div></details>
      <details><summary>What kinds of cases does the referral network take?</summary><div class="a">Primarily civil rights matters: § 1983 claims for excessive force, deliberate indifference to medical needs, unconstitutional conditions of confinement, wrongful death, and FTCA claims against federal facilities. Every case gets a free intake review to determine fit.</div></details>
      <details><summary>What if I'd rather represent myself?</summary><div class="a">Then we work for you. Our paralegals prepare habeas petitions, § 1983 complaints, motions, briefs, and appeals — for any court, federal or state, in all 50 states. Contact us for a quote tailored to your case.</div></details>
      <details><summary>How long does document preparation take?</summary><div class="a">Standard documents take 7–14 business days. Expedited service is available for urgent deadlines — call 786-408-5073 and tell us your due date.</div></details>
      <details><summary>Is my information confidential?</summary><div class="a">Absolutely. Case details and communications are kept strictly private and are never shared with third parties — including network attorneys — without your explicit consent.</div></details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

